  "prompt": "What are some interesting startups of 2014?",
  "response": "In 2014, several interesting startups emerged, representing a wide range of industries and innovative ideas. Here are some notable ones:\n\n1. **Slack** - Launched in August 2013 and gaining traction in 2014, Slack quickly became the go-to communication platform for teams, offering a seamless blend of chat, file sharing, and integrations with other software tools.\n\n2. **Magic Leap** - Founded in 2010 but gaining significant attention in 2014, Magic Leap focused on developing augmented reality and mixed reality technology. Their work on wearable devices promised to revolutionize immersive experiences.\n\n3. **Docker** - Although Docker started in 2013, 2014 was the year it exploded in popularity. Docker's containerization technology enables developers to package applications with all their dependencies into standardized units, vastly simplifying deployment and scaling.\n\n4. **Casper** - Founded in 2014, Casper disrupted the mattress industry by offering high-quality mattresses direct-to-consumer through an online platform, leveraging data-driven design and marketing strategies.\n\n5. **Zenefits** - Launched in 2013 and rapidly growing in 2014, Zenefits aimed to simplify HR management for small businesses by providing cloud-based software that integrates payroll, benefits, and compliance together.\n\n6. **Coinbase** - While Coinbase was founded in 2012, by 2014, it had established itself as one of the leading cryptocurrency exchange platforms, making it easier for consumers to buy, sell, and use Bitcoin and other cryptocurrencies.\n\n7. **Harry's** - Founded in 2013, Harry's raised considerable attention and funding in 2014 as it sought to change the shaving industry with quality razors and grooming products sold directly to consumers online.\n\n8. **Stripe** - Stripe, started in 2010, saw significant expansion in 2014. With its API-driven approach to payment processing, Stripe was streamlining online transactions for businesses globally.\n\n9. **Warby Parker** - Founded in 2010, Warby Parker continued to thrive in 2014, offering stylish eyewear at affordable prices, disrupting the traditional retail model with its direct-to-consumer approach.\n\n10. **Lending Club** - Although Lending Club was founded in 2006, in 2014 it became the first peer-to-peer lender to be publicly traded, marking a significant milestone and highlighting its impact on the financial industry.\n\nThese startups not only garnered significant attention and funding in 2014 but also demonstrated innovative approaches and solutions in their respective fields.",
